vyLGSc1kHJI.keywords: Real Madrid vs Athletic Bilbao 08 05 10 2010 HD Ronaldo Yeste Higuain Ramos Benzema MarceloReal Madrid vs Athletic Bilbao 080510 5  1 HDC.Ronaldo 22' PK 10 F.J.Yeste 41' 11 G.Higuain 73' 21 S.Ramos 80' 31 K.Benzema 81' 41 Marcelo 89' 51 Stadium Estadio Santiago Bernabu, Spain Attendance 80,000 Match Time May 8, 2010, 2000 UK Officials Csar Muiz Fernndez Referee Cristiano Ronaldo and Gonzalo Higuain were again on the scoresheet as Real Madrid ensured the Primera Division title race would go to the final week with an ultimately convincing 51 victory over 10man Athletic Bilbao. The duo had netted 51 league goals between them in 56 games prior to this fixture and they were on the mark once more as Madrid stayed within a point of leaders Barcelona, who beat Sevilla 32. Ronaldo, who struck his first hattrick for Madrid in Wednesday's 41 win over Real Mallorca, opened the scoring from the penalty spot in the 22nd minute in an incident that also saw Athletic defender Fernando Amorebieta sentoff. Athletic captain Fran Yeste threatened to ruin Madrid's night when he scored a brilliant equaliser just before halftime, but four goals in the final 17 minutes from Higuain, Sergio Ramos, Karim Benzema and Marcelo earned the home side their 18th win in their last 19 league games. Manuel Pellegrini's side are still underdogs to win the title however, as Barca are at home to lowly Real Valladolid next weekend while Madrid go to Malaga. Athletic striker Gaizka Toquero gave the home side a couple of scares early on, bringing a diving save out of Iker Casillas with a flicked header and then racing through on goal after robbing Raul Albiol only to slice wide. Aside from those incidents though it was almost all Madrid, with Ronaldo twice going close before finding it third time lucky after the home side were awarded a penalty in the 20th minute. Higuain's shot from the edge of the box struck Amorebieta's hand and not only did referee Cesar Muniz Fernandez award a penalty but he also dismissed the Athletic centreback. It looked harsh to give both the penalty and a red card, and Ronaldo added salt to Athletic's wounds by calmly rolling in the resulting penalty for his 26th goal of the season. After that it was only the goalkeeping of Gorka Iraizoz that kept Madrid from running away with the game as he denied Higuain twice and also Fernando Gago and Esteban Granero in quick succession. A second Madrid goal looked inevitable, but it was actually Athletic who found the back of the next as they stunned the Bernabeu with a superb equaliser from Yeste. There appeared little danger when the Athletic captain picked the ball up with plenty of Madrid defenders back, but he danced inside Sergio Ramos, Gago, Xabi Alonso and Albiol before driving a low shot past Casillas. That was a huge blow for Madrid, and Pellegrini responded by sending on Kaka for Gago at the break. The second period continued in a similar vein to the first, with Madrid virtually camped in the Athletic half. Ronaldo, Kaka and Marcelo all went close with headers while Granero's 20yard strike clipped the top of the crossbar. But with halfanhour to go the title was heading to Barca, and Athletic almost hammered another nail in Madrid's coffin when Yeste went close with a shot that Casillas saved with his feet. The final 25 minutes saw Madrid laying siege to the visiting goal. Higuain was proving the biggest threat and he went close three times before finally putting Madrid back in front. News had filtered through to the Bernabeu that Sevilla had trimmed Barca's lead from 30 to 32 and Madrid responded almost immediately to give the home fans further reason for optimism. Alonso's freekick was deflected goalwards off an Athletic defender, and although Iraizoz did well to palm the ball away, Higuain was perfectly placed beyond the far post to head in his 27th of the season. That was the breakthrough Madrid needed and they added three more goals through Ramos, Benzema and Marcelo late on to seal their 10th home win in 11 meetings with Athletic and keep the title race going to the wire.

Add rum for a Halloween cocktail. Stay for more This apple cider recipe isn't 100 homemade, since we bought the apple juice from the store, but adding all of the holiday spices really brings it to the next level. Holly and Hilary served this cider at last year's Halloween party and had to make three batches to keep up with demand! Here are the ingredients for the cider 12 Gallon of Unsweetened Apple Juice 1 Orange 15 Cloves count 'em out 15 Allspice berries 4 Sticks of Cinnamon can be used for garnish later! 1 Teaspoon of Nutmeg 7 Pods of Cardamon 1 cup or more of Spiced Rum per batch if you're making the cocktail version Tools You'll Need A 3quart saucepan and stove A strainer Ice if you need to cool down the batch before adding Rum. If you're making the nonalcoholic version, you don't need to cool it down before serving unless you're concerned for your safety. Since alcohol is burned off at nearboiling temperatures, we used the ice to quickly cool it before adding the rum for max impact. Thanks to Lizzy for that idea!! To actually make the cider, pour the apple juice into the saucepan and bring to a boil. Once it's boiling, you can add all of the Halloween spices and the orange cut into quarters. Bring the cider down to simmering, cover, and simmer for 20 minutes. If you're making the nonalcoholic version, just strain and serve the cider with a cinnamon stick. If you want to add rum, cool the batch down in some ice water, strain, and serve!
